HEADWORD: Thermoelectric pair
<hw>Ther`mo*e*lec"tric pair</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>.
<fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A union of two conductors, as bars or wires of
dissimilar metals joined at their extremities, for producing a
thermoelectric current.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thermoelectricity</ent>⟦br⟧
